@PryvitKyle This may not be acceptable for all use cases! Concretely, our proposal needs quite some trial-and-error decryption.  

Maybe makes sense to use them only in the "last hop"?

Or in some hops during the DIDComm route?  I guess it depends on one's privacy-efficiency requirements.

@PryvitKyle That means that, even when using OHTTPS, DIDComm messages themselves would be leaking the receiver id to in-route parties, unless our ra-anon is used.

Maybe I'm missing something, though.

In any case, it does look useful to have a more privacy-preserving communication channel.

